1. Install the OS (Ubuntu 11.04) on /dev/sda of system volume server, and configure the network.

2. Place this directory (SysVolumeServer) on the root directory (/).

3. Change your privilege to root.

2. Execute SystemVolumeDeploy.sh.

   The script will do the following things:
   (1) Install GlusterFS 3.2.3 and NFS-kernel-server
   (2) Create two directory /export1 and /export2
   (3) Mount /dev/sdb on /export2 
   (4) Create a GlusterFS volume using /export1 and /export2 as bricks (replica two)
   (5) Mount the GlusterFS volume on /SystemVolume (/SystemVolume is the directory of nfs export directory)
   (6) Return a mount point (xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:/SystemVolume)
   (7) Modify /etc/fstab to mount /dev/sdb automatically
   (8) Modify /etc/rc.local to execute ./nfs_ServiceStart.sh automatically every rebooting

